Transcription.Text: A radiant heater, dissipating 750 w at 110 v, was mounted above the workholder to raise the temperature of the substrate to 300 deg C before evaporation. The temperature of the substrate was measured by means of a chromel-alumel thermocouple placed inside the vacuum chamber with its junction resting on the top face of the workholder.
